Nigeria international striker, Asisat Oshoala, scored for the third game in a row for Barcelona, as they hammered FC Minsk 5-0 in the first leg of the last 16 of the UEFA Women’s Champions League on Thursday evening. Oshoala struck from close range to open the scoring in the 6th minute. Marta Torrejón made it 2-0 to the Spanish side in the 20th minute. Aitana increased Barcelona’s lead in the 22nd minute, following a fine assist from Oshoala and then made it 4-0 four minutes later. The Super Falcons star was replaced after an hour by Jenni Hermoso, who wrapped up the scoring with five minutes left on the clock. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.